    <xs:simpleType name="quantityType">
        <xs:annotation>
            <xs:documentation>
                The quantityType is restricting the value of the quantity attribute of the columnType.
                For data columns this attribute is used to describe the data.
                For meta data columns the attribute is used to match the data column(s) that is enriched with the meta data. 
				
				For quantities defined is restricted to strings that represent entries from the ISO 80000 series.  
				The string contains information on Item number, quantity name and unit is as follows
				
				"[Item number] | [Quantity Name] | [Unit]"
				
				Example: 
				"5-2|Celsius temperature|ã"
				
				If one needs to define a quantity not covered in the restriction list, one may use the "quantityUnitDefRef",
				in which case an "id" from quantityUnits should be provided in the quantityUnitDefRef attribute. 
				
				Included from the ISO 80000 Series
				-----------------------------------
				ISO 80000-3:2020	Space and time 
				ISO 80000-4:2020	Mechanics 
				ISO 80000-5:2019	Thermodynamics 
				ISO 80000-6:2022	Electromagnetism 
				ISO 80000-7:2019	Light 
				ISO 80000-8:2020	Acoustics 
				ISO 80000-9:2019	Physical chemistry and molecular physics 
				ISO 80000-10:2019	Atomic and nuclear physics 
				ISO 80000-11:2020	Solid state physics 

				Not included from the ISO 80000 Series
				-----------------------------------
				ISO 80000-1  General 
				ISO 80000-2  Mathematical signs and symbols to be used in the natural sciences and technology 
				ISO 80000-11 Characteristic numbers 
				ISO 80000-13 Information science and technology 
				ISO 80000-14 Telebiometrics related to human physiology 
				
				https://si-digital-framework.org/SI/
				TODO: Description on how to parse the restriction expressions. 
						5-2|Celsius Temperature|ô¯C |  
            </xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
